args: Oh no! That girl is being\nattacked by a horde of fiends!\nWe need to go save her!
I'll draw the fiends away!\nYou get the girl!
Huh? Why do you know my name?
Oh my goodness. I must be dreaming.\nTo think we'd meet here! *sniffle*
Why the sudden outpouring of emotion?
My name is Paula.\nThe truth is, I...\nI escaped from the Syndicate!
They kidnapped me and\nused me for some experiment...
Apparently, I outlived my usefulness,\nbecause they were about to dispose of me.
What a vile word—＂dispose.＂\nI knew they were evil, but hearing\nthat makes my blood boil.
The others in my test group helped\nme to escape, and entrusted me\nwith a single hope.
To find YOU, Aldred! You fought back\nagainst them and foiled so many of\ntheir schemes. You are our last hope!
I beg you! Please help everyone else\nstill stuck within the Syndicate stronghold!
I'll go, of course.\nShe had me at ＂Syndicate.＂
Oh! Thank you, truly,\nfrom the bottom of my heart!
All right, I'm gettin' PUMPED!\nLet's scrub 'em out for good\nthis time, Aldred!
I never said I was taking you with me.
This is a problem for those of us\nwho were wronged by the Syndicate. \nI don't want anyone else getting involved.
Come on, Aldred.\nI thought we were allies.
Yeah. It was a nice thought.
Shut up. I don't want allies that\njust play at being my friends.
I'm serious. If you insist on coming\nwith me, then I'll get rid of you by force.
...Fine. I won't go against your wishes.
The Syndicate is my eternal enemy.\nI won't let anyone get between me\nand my revenge. Come on, let's go.
We've made it inside the Syndicate\nfortress. ...Wait, what is that?!
AAAH HA HA HA!\nYou walked right into that one, rubbish!
You...! You were with the\nSyndicate all along!
And you didn't notice until it was\ntoo late, traitorous trash! This place\nwill be your grave!
Let me ask this: Why are you after me?\nIs it some kind of revenge?
Revenge? Hah. Our proud organization\nhas no need for such a petty notion.
I am simply enlightening a fool\nwho cannot understand the profound\nideologies of the Syndicate!
Now, fiends! Eviscerate him so I can\ndispose of him like the rubbish he is!
Didn't ya get the memo?\nIt's recyclin' day, and fiends are\non the docket, not friends.
You sure got here quick.\nYou could've taken your time.
We timed our rescue rather impeccably,\nI thought. Surely we've earned at least a\n＂thank you.＂
Maybe if you'd waited a little longer.\nI had it under control.

Sorry to break it to you, but I had a
feeling you were with the Syndicate
from the start. You forget that I'm
intimately familiar with how they operate.
But why has the seventh heir \nand his company come?!\nI saw you discuss no such stratagem!
It's simple. I didn't take Aldred at\nhis word when he said he didn't\nthink of us as allies anymore.
If that were true, he would not have\ndrawn those fiends away from us just\nmoments prior.
Indeed. That is why we immediately\nsurmised that he was laying a trap to\nmake you drop your guard.
So we crept after ya, all quiet-like.\nAnd lo and behold!
Does this prove to you that \nwe're not just pretending \nto be friends with you?
Heh. Guess it does.\nI was right to trust you guys.
Absurd. What does the seventh heir\nhave to gain from such an alliance?
Having allies isn't a zero-sum game.
I trusted in them, and they repaid\nme in full. It's that simple.
Now that's what I like to hear.
Urrrgh! I'll at least take you with me!\nDie, rubbish!
Go ahead and try.\nYou can't take me down!
Do a little soul-searching. Find someplace\nbeyond the Syndicate's reach and start a\nnew life without them.
Rgh...! Why?\nWhy won't you kill me?!
Listen. I saw the scar on your neck.\nYou weren't lying about being a\ntest subject.
The Syndicate turned my life upside-down\ntoo. I don't want to kill someone who went\nthrough the same hell I did.
D-don't take me for a fool!\nI stand before you a part of\nthe very Syndicate you despise!
You're right that I hate them.\nBut I want to stop fighting on hate alone.
Because I'm not alone anymore.\nAfter fighting alone for so long...\nI finally have allies.
